{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 20:09:51.701515", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Answer**\\n\\nThe router is never able to move past the **2‑way** state – it never becomes **Full**.  \\nThat means the two routers are not exchanging OSPF Hello packets correctly.  \\nIn this case the problem is a **mismatch in the OSPF Hello configuration** (either the Hello interval or the network type is different on the two sides). Because the Hello packets are not being received, the neighbor never reaches the Full state and the adjacency never forms. This prevents the routers from exchanging LSAs and building a complete OSPF topology, which is why the OSPF neighbor relationship fails., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8341d1fd-81d8-474d-9004-215eecd0691c'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
